---++ Quick and dirty installation steps
   * Get and install pacman from http://physics.bu.edu/pacman/
   * create new directory for vtb installation
   * run pacman -get VTB:ce-ver (replace ver with version, e.g. 180, 171) 
   * run pacman -get VTB:Globus-{JobManager}-Setup-ver (replace ver with version e.g. 180, 171)
      * !JobManager can be PBS, SGE, Condor, etc.
      * If Condor, set *VDTSETUP_CONDOR_LOCATION*  and *VDTSETUP_CONDOR_CONFIG* before running the pacman command
   * source setup.sh 
   * run ./monitoring/configure-osg.sh and answer questions
   * setup gridmap file or prima callout in /etc/grid-securitry
   * run vdt-control --on to turn on services

